#-----------------------
# Holy Unholy Knight
#-----------------------

###Block:Holy Unholy Knight
# Ability Name		Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type					Define								Description																											Ability								Save bonus						Modify VAR																												Benefits
Divine Grace		KEY:Holy Unholy Knight ~ Divine Grace		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural									DESC:You apply your Charisma modifier (if positive) as a bonus on all saving throws.																										BONUS:SAVE|Fortitude,Reflex,Will|CHA|PRESTAT:1,CHA=12																														BENEFIT:You apply your Charisma modifier (if positive) as a bonus on all saving throws.
Sense Allegiance	KEY:Holy Unholy Knight ~ Sense Allegiance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality											DESC:You can sense the presence of characters, creatures, and items of both your chosen allegiance, and your opposing allegiance in a 60-foot radius around you. Pinpoint more finely with a successful Search check (DC 25).																																													BENEFIT:You can sense the presence of characters, creatures, and items of both your chosen allegiance, and your opposing allegiance (an Holy Knight has good as a chosen allegiance, and evil as an opposing allegiance, while an Unholy Knight has the reverse). The sense allegiance ability extends in a 60-foot radius around the Knight, but may be concentrated to a quarter circle emanating forward from the Knight. You can pinpoint allegiance more finely with a successful Search check (DC 25).
Smite Allegiance	KEY:Holy Unholy Knight ~ Smite Allegiance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality											DESC:You can smite characters, creatures, or items of opposing allegiance with a single melee attack.																																																												BENEFIT:You can smite characters, creatures, or items of opposing allegiance with a single melee attack (a Holy Knight has evil as an opposing allegiance, an Unholy Knight has good as an opposing allegiance). You spend an action point and, in addition to the normal benefit of the action point, gain a bonus to the attack equal to your Charisma modifier (if positive) and deal 1 extra point of damage per character level (your character level, not the target's). Should the attack miss, the action point is expended. Similarly, the action point is expended if you use it and strike a target that does not have an opposing allegiance. Smite allegiance is considered a supernatural ability.
Divine Touch		KEY:Holy Unholy Knight ~ Divine Touch		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality											DESC:You can channel divine energy through your body and apply it directly to yourself or another character.																																																											BENEFIT:you can channel divine energy through your body and apply it directly to yourself or another character. With this ability you can restore lost hit points with a single touch; you may also choose to deal holy damage to a target with a simple a touch attack. Each day you may cure or deal a number of points of damage equal to your Charisma bonus times your total character level. A Holy Knight is not limited to curing wounds, nor is an Unholy Knight restricted to inflicting them. It is possible to combine this ability with smite allegiance to increase the amount of damage dealt by a touch attack. Massive damage rules apply. Use of this ability may be guided by the your allegiance, and widespread abuse may cause the you to lose your chosen allegiance.
Turn Undead		KEY:Holy Unholy Knight ~ Turn Undead		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			DEFINE:ExtraTurningQual|0	DEFINE:ImprovedTurningQual|0	DESC:You can turn undead in the same manner as an Acolyte.																					ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Base Turn|Turn/Rebuke Undead								BONUS:VAR|ExtraTurningQual|1	BONUS:VAR|ImprovedTurningQual|1	BONUS:VAR|TurnCheck|CHA|TYPE=Stat	BONUS:VAR|TurnDamagePlus|HolyUnholyKnightLVL	BONUS:VAR|TurnLevel|HolyUnholyKnightLVL	BONUS:VAR|TurnTimes|3+CHA|TYPE=Stat	BENEFIT:You can turn undead in the same manner as an Acolyte. A Holy Knight affects undead in the same manner as an Acolyte with good allegiance (turning or destroying undead), while an Unholy Knight affects undead in the same manner as an Acolyte with evil allegiance (rebuking or commanding them). Count all Holy/Unholy Knight and Acolyte levels when determining level for purposes of turning.


